description.narrative: A total of 150,423 children under five were screened for malnutrition, from which 16,659 found with SAM and admitted for treatment between January and May 2020. A total 122 nutrition and health workers from 6 drought and COVID-19 most-affected provinces were trained remotely on simplified protocols for SAM management. Drought emergency response in the south of Angola is ongoing with critical WASH activities being implemented by UNICEF implementing partners in Bíé, Cuando Cubango, Cunene, Huíla and Namibe. Birth registration services continue to be operational despite government lockdown, with control measures to mitigate the risks of COVID-19. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/08/2020
